Going to edit my review as we keep coming back, been here over a dozen times  The service will probably never be top notch. It's not terrible but don't expect anything out of the ordinary. We're regular so they take care of us a bit more. It's a small, seems family run, restaurant with good options on food. The food is GOOD and the prices are reasonable.  Every dish we've tried has been good. Beef stew, roasted chicken, tostones, empanadas, and bbq chicken, to name a few.  Not the trendiest place but they crank, more so through deliveries. That's why the in house service could be a bit slow at times. When not busy with deliveries they're good with in house service.  Highly recommended. Great food, nice people, good prices, nice place.
